Notice on intended use

This software is research code developed as part of a Master's thesis on
machine learning applied to Active Directory security. It is released for
educational, academic, and defensive security research purposes, and for
authorised penetration testing engagements.

The author makes no representations about the Software's suitability for any
other use. Users are solely responsible for ensuring that any use complies
with all applicable laws, regulations, and authorisation requirements for the
target environment. The author disclaims any responsibility for misuse or for
consequences arising from use of this Software against systems for which the
user does not hold explicit authorisation.

The techniques and attack-path discovery methods implemented here rely on
publicly documented Active Directory security research, including work
published by SpecterOps (BloodHound), Will Schroeder, Lee Christensen,
Charlie Bromberg, and many others in the offensive security community.